description:
In lichen_l2_enable() when re-enabling, lichen_lora_l2_get_eui64() could return NULL if LoRa L2 was deinitialized during the enable/disable cycle:

```c
const uint8_t *eui64 = lichen_lora_l2_get_eui64();
if (eui64 == NULL) {
    LOG_ERR("Cannot re-init link_ctx: LoRa L2 not initialized");
    k_mutex_unlock(&rx_mutex);
    k_mutex_unlock(&tx_mutex);
    return -ENODEV;
}
```

This check IS present. Code is correct.

However, at line 671, lichen_link_init() is called with eui64 which has been validated. No issue here. Closing.
